		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Olle Linge]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Advanced]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Beginner]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Immersion and integration]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Intermediate]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Reading]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Uncategorised]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Vocabulary]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Extensive reading]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Intensive reading]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Reading comprehension]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Sinosplice]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.hackingchinese.com/?p=8622</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>Extensive reading is when you read more text at a higher level of comprehension (around 98%), which should be contrasted by intensive reading when you need assistance to understand the text. Most courses focus only on intensive reading, but you should actually spend most of your time on extensive reading.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hackingchinese.com/introduction-extensive-reading-chinese-learners/">An introduction to extensive reading for Chinese learners</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.hackingchinese.com">Hacking Chinese</a>.</p>
]]></description>
